How do we protect the personal data we process?
What is our policy regarding children's privacy?
How do we use cookies or similar technologies?
3. What Personal Data Do We Process?
We process only the necessary data that you provide or leave while using Replaio Services, as well as data from our partners. These are primarily data necessary to provide Replaio Services, including providing you with access to a Replaio account. You can use Replaio Services anonymously — without creating a Replaio account. However, this does not preclude us from processing personal data.
Providing certain personal data is voluntary, but not providing it in the case of some services will prevent their provision.
More information on what data we process can be found in the next section, “Purposes of Data Processing.”
4. For What Purpose and On What Basis Do We Process Personal Data?
The primary purposes for processing your data are:
providing Replaio Services available through the Replaio application or the websites
repla.io
,
blog.repla.io
,
fulfilling our legal or contractual obligations,
realizing our legitimate interests.
When you start using our services, e.g., by installing the Replaio Radio app or visiting our websites or online services, you accept and enter into an agreement with us in accordance with our
Terms of Use
. According to this agreement, we are obligated to provide you with services, which requires processing personal data.
4.1. Purposes of Data Processing
4.1.1. Provision and Personalization of Replaio Services
To provide services to users who do not use the login option (without a Replaio Account), we process data concerning the user's device, the device's IP address, the information contained in cookies or other similar technologies, and session data.
To offer Replaio Services tailored to the user's location (e.g., suggesting local radio stations), it is necessary to process location data. To provide Replaio services, the user's device IP address is processed. This simplified “geolocation” i.e., assigning the service provision location, is based solely on the IP address. The information obtained in this way does not allow for precise information about the user's actual location.
When providing services to users with a Replaio Account, we additionally process:
information necessary for account registration: email address and password,
additional, optional information provided for Replaio account identification: identifier (nickname) or first and last name,
information necessary for logging in through other services: Facebook, Google, Huawei: email address, first name, last name, avatar,
in the case of additional, paid options available in Replaio Services – information about the payment made.
Using a Replaio account requires providing authentication data: email address and password. Providing the first and last name is voluntary, and the user can add it at any time as account-identifying data.
We process this data to provide services, i.e., to fulfil the contract. The legal basis for collecting and processing personal data is Article 6(1)(b) of the GDPR.
4.1.2. Contact implementation
When contacting our users regarding technical support and use of the application and collecting opinions about the application, we process the e-mail address and the content of the message.
We process this data to provide services, i.e., perform the contract and for the legitimate interest of ensuring contact with users. The legal basis for the collection and processing of personal data is Art. 6 section 1 letter b and art. 6 section 1 letter f GDPR.
4.1.2. Newsletter
For users who voluntarily subscribe to the Newsletter service, we provide a service of delivering messages with information related to Replaio Services. For this purpose, we process the email address provided by the user during registration.
The email addresses provided, for this purpose, are processed to fulfil the contract following Article 6(1)(b) of the GDPR.
As part of the Newsletter service, we may send users marketing content promoting Replaio services and products, as well as those of our partners. Personal data in this case is processed based on legitimate interest under Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.
The email address used within the Newsletter service may also be processed to potentially establish, investigate, or defend against claims. The legal basis for processing is our legitimate interest according to Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR, which involves protecting our rights.
4.1.3. Diagnostics, troubleshooting, development, development of new features, and improvements to Replaio Services
To improve the quality of our services, we may process information regarding the use of Replaio Services, including session information, IP address, time spent using Replaio Services on individual screens, pages, and subpages, and the use of features and content.
We process this data to provide services, i.e., to fulfil the contract, and in our legitimate interest, which involves creating solutions to facilitate service usage and improving the quality and functionality of the services provided. The legal basis for collecting and processing personal data is Article 6(1)(b) and Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.
4.1.4. Statistics
For statistical analysis of service usage, Replaio uses services provided by Google Ireland Limited: Google Analytics and Google Firebase, a service provided by:
