https://policies.google.com/privacy
.
The legal basis for processing data is Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.
4.1.5. Marketing, Promotion, and Advertising
Direct Marketing
We do not use personal data, including email addresses and other identity-related data of users, for marketing purposes of other entities. However, we may occasionally send information about our promotional activities in the form of email messages or push notifications directly within the application.
To partially cover the costs of maintenance, we place advertisements in our services delivered by our partners. To deliver ads and content more tailored to user interests, our partners may use advertising identifiers or similar technologies.
Interest-Based Personalized Advertising
Profiling for marketing purposes is carried out by our trusted partners, subject to your consent. Consent is voluntary and can be given through a message displayed during the consent collection process. You can withdraw consent at any time.
The delivery of ads tailored to user interests is done using unique identifiers. We do not combine this information with user identity information.
