4.1.6. Investigative Procedures, Claims Investigation
In cases related to breaches of the Terms of Use or legal regulations, procedures for asserting our claims, and defending against claims from users or other entities, we may process personal data of specific users.
If personal data is processed to assert the claims of other users, this data may be disclosed to other users and entities, or to public authorities authorized by law, such as courts, police, or prosecutors.
We will process and, if necessary, disclose this data to fulfil our legal obligations, i.e., in our legitimate interest of asserting our claims against the user. The legal basis for collecting and processing your data is Article 6(1)(c) of the GDPR.
4.1.7. Ensuring Legal Compliance
We may process personal data to fulfill legal obligations related to our activities and requests from law enforcement authorities. The legal basis for such processing of personal data is compliance with applicable legal regulations and our legitimate interest. The legal basis for collecting and processing your data is Article 6(1)(c) and Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.
4.1.8.  Social Media
Facebook
As part of managing profiles on social media platforms such as Facebook, we may have access to anonymized data of Facebook users who visit and are active on the Replaio fan page. The legal basis for processing such data is our legitimate interest based on Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR, which involves promoting our brand.
While using the Facebook service provided by Meta Ireland, Replaio acts as a joint data controller for data concerning users' use of the Replaio fan page. More information about this data processing method can be found at:
https://www.facebook.com/legal/terms/page_controller_addendum
.
4.1.9. Other Services
Spotify
As part of the option to create playlists of favorite songs on Spotify available from within the Replaio Radio application, we may process data necessary to integrate Replaio with the user's Spotify account. For this purpose, we may process the user's identifier in the Spotify service. We process this data to fulfil the contract following Article 6(1)(b) of the GDPR.
The collection and processing of data by Spotify are carried out in accordance with the privacy policies, which are available at:
https://www.spotify.com/pl/legal/privacy-policy
.
Algolia
Providing users with a search engine for radio station addresses in Replaio's index, we use the services of Algolia Inc. The service allows for a very quick search for radio stations' web addresses based on keywords entered by users. These data, together with the IP address, are process this data to fulfil the contract following Article 6(1)(b) of the GDPR.
The collection and processing of data by Algolia Inc. are carried out in accordance with the privacy policies, which are available at:
https://www.spotify.com/pl/legal/privacy-policy
.
5. What rights do you have?
The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) grants individuals-specific rights regarding their data.
The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) grants individuals certain rights regarding their personal data. Replaio ensures that users of its services are able to exercise these rights, subject to the technical possibilities and limitations of applicable law.
By using Replaio services, you are entitled to the following rights regarding the processing of your data:
Right to access data
You are entitled to be informed about the personal data we process, and you can request access to this data.
Right to rectification and completion of data
You can correct your data. If you become aware that your data processed by us is incorrect, outdated, or incomplete, you are entitled to request immediate rectification or completion.
Right to erasure of data
A user who has created a Replaio account can request its deletion at any time.
Sending a request to delete a Replaio account from within the app
Log in to your Replaio account.
Go to the Menu and select Account.
Click the more icon (three dots) and select the Delete account option.
Sending a request to delete a Replaio account from a web browser
Go to the website
https://account.repla.io/delete-account
and read its content.
Click "Log in" and log in to your Replaio account.
Select the "Delete account" option and confirm the deletion of your Replaio account.
Right to restriction of data processing
You are entitled to temporarily or permanently cease the processing of all or some of your data.
Right to object
You can object at any time to the processing of your data by us.
Right to data portability
You are entitled to data portability – you can request a copy of your data in electronic form and the right to transfer it to another entity for use in providing services by that entity.
Right to complain with a supervisory authority
You are entitled to complain with a supervisory authority responsible for data protection.
6. How long do we store personal data?
We store personal data for as long as necessary for:
providing services at the highest level,
business interests related to the development and improvement of provided services,
ensuring compliance with legal obligations,
resolving claims and disputes.
Most data is retained only for the duration of your use of Replaio Services.
Personal data collected during the provision of Replaio Services will be deleted when it is no longer needed to achieve the purpose of storage.
User personal data will be deleted after consent for such processing and storage is withdrawn, as appropriate.
Deletion does not include data the correction, blocking, or deletion of which is contrary to statutory or contractual storage periods, as well as data necessary to establish, exercise, or change the contractual relationship between Replaio and the user.
7. Do we share data, and where can it be processed?
We do not transfer personal data outside the EU or the EEA unless necessary. However, some of our partners and service providers may be based in, or their servers may be located in another country. All operations related to such transfer of personal data are carried out following the regulations governing the processing of personal data, in particular the GDPR. We ensure that third-party recipients apply standard contractual clauses compliant with EU law.
Service providers with whom we collaborate to provide Replaio services
In order to provide Replaio services at the highest level and in accordance with the law, we may share certain data with trusted entities collaborating with us:
hosting service providers who provide us with certified and secure IT resources,
Internet and analytical service providers.
The transfer of data to service providers is carried out solely based on appropriate cooperation agreements that comply with the regulations governing the processing of personal data, particularly the GDPR.
