9.How do we protect personal data?
We respect the personal data of our users and strive to provide them with the highest possible level of protection. We operate following applicable law and use reasonable administrative, logical and physical safeguards designed to protect personal data against loss, theft, unauthorized access, use, or modification. These safeguards are intended to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risks associated with the processing of our users' data. We have implemented and applied various data protection policies, including pseudonymization, data encryption, and access control, and the data is stored in certified, secure Data Centers.
10. Protecting children's privacy. Do we collect data from children?
Our services are not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect information about them. If we become aware that a person under the age of 13 has provided us with their data, we will immediately delete it.
If you have information that a child under the age of 13, or a child over the age of 13 without parental consent, has provided us with personal data, please contact us. If we learn that we have collected any personal data from children that we should not process, or for which parents have not given consent, we will take immediate steps to delete such data.
11. Cookie Policy (including similar technologies)
Replaio services, including repla.io, blog.repla.io, and the Replaio Radio application, may utilize technical capabilities provided by web beacons, such as cookies or similar technologies, including unique identifiers. Throughout this document, all such solutions will be referred to as “cookies”.
Cookies, which may be stored on a computer, smartphone, or tablet when visiting websites and internet services, are used to collect and store information about user activity. This allows user preferences to be used for displaying more relevant search results, delivering expected content, or displaying advertisements and promotional offers tailored to user interests.
Cookies typically contain the domain name of the internet service, from which they originate, a unique identifier, and the duration of their storage on the device.
For what purpose do we use cookies?
We use cookies or similar technologies on the repla.io and blog.repla.io websites in the Replaio Services for the following purposes.
We provide services, including maintaining user sessions after logging in, so that users do not have to re-enter their login and password on each subpage.
Optimization efforts are undertaken to ensure our services and pages operate faster and are easier to use.
We conduct analyses and gather statistics to understand how users interact with our services and pages. This enables us to develop and tailor our services to meet user expectations and needs.
We facilitate the presentation of advertisements to users based on their interests.
What types of cookies do we use?
Necessary cookies – ensure the proper functioning of the websites and their basic functions. Without them, users would not be able to properly use the services available on the websites.
Analytical cookies – our websites use cookies provided by Google Analytics. Analytical cookies enable us to track the number and source of visits so that we can measure and improve the performance of our services. This type of cookies helps us understand which pages are most or least visited and how visitors use our services. We also cooperate with external partners who provide us with analytical tools, e.g., Google Analytics. Google uses its cookies in this case. More information about how Google uses cookies can be found at
How Google uses cookies
.
Marketing cookies – our services use the capabilities of third-party cookies to target and display advertisements and promotional offers. This allows us to partially fund the development of our services by displaying banner ads, video ads and promotional offers that are well-tailored to your interests and online activity. In this case, we use the services of external advertising service providers, including Google. For more information on how Google uses cookies to serve ads, please visit:
How Google uses cookies to serve ads
.
Consent management and legal compliance
To ensure transparency and control over the processing of personal data for our users, we use practices consistent with IAB Europe standards. It is a European association dealing, among other things, with developing standards in the field of digital marketing, advertising, and the processing of personal data. IAB has developed the TCF (The Transparency & Consent Framework) standard, which helps implement solutions in compliance with legal regulations regarding privacy and personal data processing, in particular with the GDPR.
More information about the TCF standard can be found on the IAB Europe website:
iabeurope.eu
.
As part of the Replaio Services, we have implemented a tool for managing consents regarding the processing of personal data, in particular for the processing of Cookies or similar technologies, hereinafter referred to as CMP (Consent Management Platform). This tool is provided by Didomi —
didomi.io
. And is certified by IAB Europe and Google. Didomi's privacy policy is available at:
didomi.io/privacy-policy
.
Users of Replaio Services, thanks to the CMP tool, can control how Replaio, our partners and other parties use the opportunities provided by cookies or similar technologies.
Most of our advertising partners are IAB Europe certified suppliers. You can see the list of all partners directly in the Replaio Radio application in the consent management window (CMP).
Our CMP tool may not be available or may look different depending on your location.
As part of the use of the CMP tool, information may be saved on the user's device, including cookies or unique identifiers used to save settings regarding consent to the processing of personal data. We process this data to provide services, i.e., perform the contract and in a legitimate interest following Art. 6 section 1 letter f GDPR.
No consent to save cookies or similar technologies
If a user does not want cookies or similar technologies to be used on their devices, they can choose an option to block their use. However, we would like to emphasize that blocking all cookies and similar technologies may negatively affect the performance, efficiency, and convenience of using our services and websites, and some features may become unavailable.
Mobile device identifiers and settings
Ustawienia w urządzeniach lub usługach, z których korzystają użytkownicy, mogą udostępniać dodatkowe opcje pozwalające na rezygnację z dopasowywania reklam i ofert promocyjnych do zainteresowań i aktywności w internecie. Na przykład w systemie Android lub usługach Google użytkownik może skorzystać z opcji „Usuń identyfikator wyświetlania reklam”. Na urządzeniach z systemem iOS dostępna jest opcja "Spersonalizowane reklamy".
Settings on devices or services that users use may provide additional options to opt out of tailored ads and promotional offers based on interests and online activity. For example, on the Android system or Google services, users can use the “Opt out of Ads Personalization” option. On iOS devices, there is an option called "Personalized ads".
12. The supervisory authority
The supervisory authority for the protection of personal data in Poland is the President of the Personal Data Protection Office with its registered office in Warsaw, ul. Stawki 2, e-mail address: kancelaria@giodo.gov.pl. You are entitled to complain to the Personal Data Protection Office in any case if you believe that your data is being processed incorrectly.
13. Changes to the Privacy Policy
This privacy policy may be modified to keep it current
and reliable information about the processing of personal data.
If the changes are material, we will notify you by displaying information
on the Replaio Services or by sending an email. We reserve the right to notify you in advance of changes to the privacy policy.
